					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "AE02000000000010"
					item: "ae2:printed_engineering_processor"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "AE02000000000011"
					item: "ae2:printed_silicon"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "Printed Circuits"
			x: 3.0d
			y: -5.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["AE01000000000005"]
			description: ["Fluix Crystals are synthesized by throwing Charged Certus Quartz, Nether Quartz, and Redstone into the same water source block simultaneously. The three items react and produce Fluix Crystals after a short delay. Fluix is the primary material for ME cables, cell components, cores, and most networking parts — consumption is continuous and has no crafting substitute. Maintain a dedicated synthesis pool near your base and keep it stocked; Fluix production is a silent bottleneck that halts expansion the moment the pool runs dry."]
			id: "AE01000000000008"
			rewards: [{
				count: 8
				id: "AE03000000000008"
				item: "ae2:fluix_crystal"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "AE02000000000012"
				item: "ae2:fluix_crystal"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Fluix Crystal"
			x: -3.0d
			y: -7.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["AE01000000000006"]
			description: ["ME Cables carry the channel signal between network components. Glass Cable carries 8 channels and is the cheapest option. Covered Cable also carries 8 and prevents color bleed between adjacent cables. Smart Cable shows live channel utilization via color indicators — use it to identify congested segments before they cause component dropouts. Dense Covered Cable carries 32 channels and is required for high-density runs between Controllers and distribution nodes. Run Smart Dense Cable on your network spine so saturation is always visible."]
			id: "AE01000000000009"
			rewards: [{
				count: 16
				id: "AE03000000000009"
				item: "ae2:fluix_covered_cable"
				type: "item"
