		{
			dependencies: ["AE01000000000016"]
			description: ["The ME Interface acts as a bidirectional buffer between the ME network and external inventories or machines. Unlike the Pattern Provider which only pushes, the Interface can both supply items from the network and accept returns into it. They are most commonly used in complex autocrafting trees where crafted intermediates need to buffer before further processing, or as a universal input point for machines that don't use dedicated GT ME bus integration. The Ex Interface (from ExtendedAE) handles higher item throughput and supports more simultaneous transfer channels for large machine clusters."]
			id: "AE01000000000021"
