		{
			dependencies: ["AE01000000000024"]
			description: ["GTCEu Stocking Input Buses and Hatches maintain a target stock level in the machine's input buffer rather than only pulling when a crafting job is active. The stocking bus monitors current inventory and replenishes from the network whenever stock drops below a configured threshold. This eliminates startup delay on machines running a single recipe continuously — the next batch of ingredients is always pre-loaded before the previous run finishes. ExpandedGT adds expanded and tag-filter stocking variants with higher per-tick transfer rates for multi-slot machines with complex ingredient mixes."]
			id: "AE01000000000026"
